<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-root-mean-squared-error">Root Mean S=
quared Error</h3>



<p>The Root Mean Squared Error is the square root of the variance of the re=
siduals. It specifies the absolute fit of the model to the data i.e. how cl=
ose the observed data points are to the predicted values. Mathematically it=
 can be represented as,</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img loading=3D"lazy" de=
coding=3D"async" width=3D"443" height=3D"80" src=3D"https://cdn.analyticsvi=
dhya.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/23186rmse.webp" alt=3D"Root Mean Square=
d Error&nbsp;" class=3D"wp-image-196053" style=3D"width:864px;height:auto">=
</figure></div>


<p>To make this estimate unbiased, one has to divide the sum of the squared=
 residuals by the <strong>degrees of freedom</strong> rather than the total=
 number of data points in the model. This term is then called the <strong>R=
esidual Standard Error(RSE)</strong>. Mathematically it can be represented =
as,</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full is-resized"><img loading=3D"lazy" de=
coding=3D"async" width=3D"449" height=3D"75" src=3D"https://cdn.analyticsvi=
dhya.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/35137rse.webp" alt=3D"Residual Standard=
 Error" class=3D"wp-image-196054" style=3D"width:832px;height:auto"></figur=
e></div>


<p>R-squared is a better measure than RSME. Because the value of&nbsp;Root =
Mean Squared Error depends on the units of the variables (i.e. it is not a =
normalized measure), it can change with the change in the unit of the varia=
bles.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-assumptions-of-linear-regression">As=
sumptions of Linear Regression</h2>



<p>Regression is a parametric approach, which means that it makes assumptio=
ns about the data for analysis. For successful regression analysis, it=E2=
=80=99s essential to validate the following assumptions.</p>



<ol class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>&nbsp;Linearity of residuals</strong>:&nbsp;There needs to be a=
 linear relationship between the dependent variable and independent variabl=
e(s).</li>
</ol>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full"><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"a=
sync" width=3D"626" height=3D"197" src=3D"https://cdn.analyticsvidhya.com/w=
p-content/uploads/2024/09/25294Screenshot_1.webp" alt=3D"Linearity of resid=
uals" class=3D"wp-image-196055"></figure></div>


<ol start=3D"2" class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Independence of residuals: </strong>The error terms should not =
be dependent on one another (like in time-series data wherein the next valu=
e is dependent on the previous one). There should be no correlation between=
 the residual terms. The absence of this phenomenon is known as <strong>Aut=
ocorrelation.</strong></li>
</ol>



<p><span style=3D"font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;">There should not b=
e any visible patterns in the error terms.</span></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full"><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=
=3D"async" width=3D"772" height=3D"239" src=3D"https://cdn.analyticsvidhya.=
com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/image-359.png" alt=3D"Linearity of residuals=
" class=3D"wp-image-171059"></figure>



<ol start=3D"3" class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Normal distribution of residuals:</strong> The mean of residual=
s should follow a <strong><a href=3D"https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2=
021/05/normal-distribution-an-ultimate-guide/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noo=
pener noreferrer">normal distribution</a></strong> with a mean equal to zer=
o or close to zero. This is done to check whether the selected line is the =
line of best fit or not. If the error terms are non-normally distributed, s=
uggests that there are a few unusual data points that must be studied close=
ly to make a better model.</li>
</ol>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full"><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"a=
sync" width=3D"785" height=3D"218" src=3D"https://cdn.analyticsvidhya.com/w=
p-content/uploads/2024/09/85436Screenshot_3.webp" alt=3D"Normal distributio=
n of residual" class=3D"wp-image-196056"></figure></div>


<p><strong>4. The equal variance of residuals:</strong>&nbsp;The error term=
s must have constant variance. This phenomenon is known as&nbsp;<strong>Hom=
oscedasticity</strong>. The presence of non-constant variance in the error =
terms is referred to as&nbsp;<strong>Heteroscedasticity</strong>. Generally=
, non-constant variance arises in the presence of&nbsp;<em>outliers or extr=
eme leverage values</em>.</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
