code><button class=3D"copy-button btn btn-dark rounded-3 fs-12">Copy Code</=
button></pre>



<p>One can see the values of betas using the following code,</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-code"><code data-highlighted=3D"yes" class=3D"hljs l=
anguage-bash"><span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Print the parameters,i.e. inte=
rcept and slope of the regression line obtained</span>
lr.params</code><button class=3D"copy-button btn btn-dark rounded-3 fs-12">=
Copy Code</button></pre>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img loading=3D"lazy"=
 decoding=3D"async" width=3D"752" height=3D"145" src=3D"https://cdn.analyti=
csvidhya.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/22681params.webp" alt=3D"lr.ramas" =
class=3D"wp-image-196065" style=3D"width:872px"></figure>



<p>Here, 6.948 is the intercept, and 0.0545 is a slope for the variable TV.=
</p>



<p>Now, let=E2=80=99s see the evaluation metrics for this linear regression=
 operation. You can simply view the summary using the following code,</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-code"><code data-highlighted=3D"yes" class=3D"hljs l=
anguage-bash"><span class=3D"hljs-comment">#Performing a summary operation =
lists out all different parameters of the regression line fitted</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(lr.summary())</code><button clas=
s=3D"copy-button btn btn-dark rounded-3 fs-12">Copy Code</button></pre>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img loading=3D"lazy"=
 decoding=3D"async" width=3D"801" height=3D"476" src=3D"https://cdn.analyti=
