<p>We are getting a decent score for both train and test sets.</p>



<p>Apart from `statsmodels`, there is another package namely `sklearn` that=
 can be used to perform linear regression. We will use the `linear_model` l=
ibrary from `sklearn` to build the model. Since we have already performed a=
 train-test split, we don=E2=80=99t need to do it again.</p>



<p>There=E2=80=99s one small step that we need to add, though. When there=
=E2=80=99s only a single feature, we need to add an additional column in or=
der for the linear regression fit to be performed successfully. Code is giv=
en below,</p>



<pre class=3D"wp-block-code"><code data-highlighted=3D"yes" class=3D"hljs l=
anguage-ini"><span class=3D"hljs-attr">X_train_lm</span> =3D X_train_lm.val=
ues.reshape(-<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-numbe=
r">1</span>)
<span class=3D"hljs-attr">X_test_lm</span> =3D X_test_lm.values.reshape(-<s=
pan class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>)</c=
ode><button class=3D"copy-button btn btn-dark rounded-3 fs-12">Copy Code</b=
utton></pre>



